lektierte transgenerische Narratologie des Dramas. Sie gestaltet neue analytische Begrifflichkeiten wie die der dramatischen Erzählinstanz und der Bühnendiegese sowie eine neue Explikation und Differenzierung eines epischen und auch eines dramatischen Erzählverfahrens.  aThis monograph builds upon transgeneric narratology to develop a new model of epization in drama. It differentiates between different diegetic levels (stage diegesis and free diegesis) as well as the narrative authority of the drama (dramatic authority). The adapted model of epization establishes epic and dramatic procedures as options for the narrative representation of a story.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aDrama. 4aErzähler. 4aNarratologie. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Drama.2bisacsh  aNarratology.  adrama.  astory-tellers.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1z978311076249508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2017z9783110548198oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831104869330 cprintz978311048071940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311048815940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110488159423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110488159/original  a978-3-11-071954-3  DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-076249-5  DG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aZDB-23-DKUb2017